  "commentary": "With SPX at 6561.91 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6550 (-6930.9M) and positive gamma at 6590 (+1010.9M), dealers are in a precarious hedging position where they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6550 and sell any push toward 6590, creating whipsaw action in this narrow 40-point range. The BREAKOUT regime with -51B total GEX means any sustained move outside this range will be amplified as dealers chase momentum—particularly dangerous given the wall_break and gex_surge events just triggered. Watch 6550 as the critical support where dealer buying should emerge, and 6590 as the resistance where dealer selling kicks in, with a break of either level likely producing explosive directional moves.\n\nBottom line: expect violent whipsaw moves between 6550-6590 until one side breaks decisively.",
